Name: COMMAND AND CONTROL MODE
Explanation: THE MODE OF ACTIVATION OF A COMMAND AND CONTROL UNIT.

Name: COMMAND AND CONTROL FUNCTION
Explanation: THE TYPE OF COMMAND AND CONTROL FUNCTION AVAILABLE FOR TASKING.REFERENCE DOCUMENTS: AJP-1, STANAG 3596, BI-MNC REPORTING DIRECTIVE VOL III ACE AIR SUPPLEMENT, ATP-27(B), ATP-34(A), ATP-44, STANAG 2434.

Name: TYPE OF COMMAND AND CONTROL AGENCY
Explanation: THE TYPE OF COMMAND AND CONTROL AGENCY AVAILABLE FOR TASKING.REFERENCE DOCUMENTS: AJP-1, STANAG 3596, BI-MNC REPORTING DIRECTIVE VOL III ACE AIR SUPPLEMENT, ATP-27(B), ATP-34(A), ATP-44, STANAG 2434.

Name: GROUND AGENCY TYPE
Explanation: TYPE OF AIR OPERATIONS COORDINATION (EXCLUDING FORWARD AIR CONTROL) ELEMENTS (FIXED OR MOBILE) LOCATED ON THE GROUND OR ON THE SURFACE.RELATED DOCUMENT: AJP-3.3

Name: COMMAND, CONTROL AND SURVEILLANCE ROLE
Explanation: TYPE OF AIR COMMAND, CONTROL AND SURVEILLANCE ROLES (INCLUDING FACS).RELATED DOCUMENT: AJP-3.3

Name: TARGET NOMINATING AUTHORITY
Explanation: THE COMMAND AND CONTROL ACENGY THAT PROVIDES THE TARGET NOMINATION.

Name: FUNCTION OF ID-GATE
Explanation: SPECIFIES THE FUNCTION OF AN IDENTIFICATION GATE USED FOR AIRCRAFT CONTROL PURPOSES.

Name: TACTICAL BATTLE MANAGEMENT FUNCTION (TBMF)
Explanation: FOR VALID TBMF SEE REFERENCE DOCUMENT SDP 10901 "ANGRY HASP" (NATINADS) (NC).

Name: AIRBORNE SURVEILLANCE, COMMAND AND CONTROL ROLE
Explanation: TYPES OF AIRBORNE SURVEILLANCE, COMMAND AND CONTROL ROLES.

Name: DEFENDED ASSET NOMINATING AUTHORITY
Explanation: THE COMMAND AND CONTROL ACENGY THAT PROVIDES THE DEFENDED ASSET NOMINATION.

Name: TYPE OF COMMAND AND CONTROL AGENCY, OTHER
Explanation: THE COMMAND AND CONTROL ACENGY NOT INCLUDED IN THE CODES LIST AVAILABLE FOR TASKING, USING LITERAL VALUE.

Name: PLACE FUNCTION
Explanation: THE PURPOSE OR FUNCTION OF A MARITIME PLACE.
